Why is fuzzy logic not popular anymore?
I think it’s because most use cases for fuzzy logic can be accomplished with Bayesian techniques and graphical models.
If the interpretation of a variable depends on context (for example, being 1m85 tall makes you a very tall person in most cases, but not if you’re hanging out with a bunch of NBA players), then you can just add variables that describe the context to the graphical model. A Bayesian approach has several advantages; everything is formally specified and you can get confidence intervals and risk assessment; those things are harder with fuzzy logic. Fuzzy logic is much more ad-hoc.)
